explanation:
This is shown by subtracting the real trajectory (with gravity) from the trajectory without gravity, which would have hit the monkey on the branch. That is, \begin{align}
x_{\text{no-grav}}(t) &= \left[ v_0 \cos \alpha \right] t \\
x_{\text{grav}}(t) &= \left[ v_0 \cos \alpha \right] t - \frac{1}{2} g t^2 \\
\text{Delta Pos.} &= x_{\text{no-grav}}(t) - x_{\text{grav}}(t) = \frac{1}{2} g t^2 
\end{align}
